    "summary": "With a new law cutting Medicaid funding to certain clinics, Planned Parenthood estimates 200 of its clinics in 24 states are at risk of closure with the cuts, and nearly all of those clinics \u2014 90% \u2014 are in states where abortion is legal. (Photo by Kayla Bartkowski/Getty Images) A federal judge ruled Friday against the Trump administration\u2019s efforts to strip Medicaid funds from primarily Planned Parenthood-affiliated abortion providers. Massachusetts U.S. District Judge Indira Talwani denied the federal government\u2019s motion to lift a block on a new law, rejecting the U.S. Department of Justice\u2019s argument that allowing Planned Parenthood to continue to bill for Medicaid while their lawsuit plays out would cause the government \u201cirreparable injury.\u201d She said the plaintiffs were more likely to suffer injury if the provision went into effect, such as having to close clinics and reduce services. \u201cHere, Defendants suffer no irreparable harm where Plaintiffs are substantially likely to succeed i...",
